When url is an empty string (""), &url[1] points one past the array. The code then calls string functions (strstr(&url[1], ".."), strrchr(&url[1], '.')) and passes &url[1] to open(). These operations will attempt to read starting at an out‑of‑bounds location, causing accesses beyond the bounds of the object and thus violating MISRA C 2023 Rule 21.17.
